Fault Slip Potential (FSP) is designed to help understand the probability of injection-induced seismicity associated with a single triggering mechanism, 
using the smallest number of input parameters possible while still being useful.
There are other potentially plausible inducement scenarios that are not considered, including fluid migration into the basement, 
out-of-zone poroelastic stressing, or hydraulic fracturing.

None of the individual models produced by Fault Slip Potential accurately represent what is happening in the subsurface.
